MoTa:
we are seeking a motivated engineering manager to help lead nab’s digital transformation efforts and reach your full potential by developing innovative products with cutting-edge cloud and microservices technologies.the successful applicant will be accountable for the leadership of one or more engineering scrum teams to plan, deliver and support service features that deliver customer value and/or mature service capability.the position is also accountable for executing the people leader fundamentals in line with nab policies, driving a learning-based culture with an ability to set and gain agreement for realistic and stretching objectives for the team.your job responsibilities 
manage multi agile teams to deliver on engineering standards, sprint backlogs, and plans, engineers’ responsibilities and performance management, code quality, adherence to development, and testing guardrails.
manage milestones, deliverables, risks, and dependencies of the engineering teams.
educate the engineering teams and ensure the release of features to production comply with nab risk management frameworks.
ability to create and maintain relationships with a wide range of stakeholders
be the voice of reason between speed and quality;
evangelist of the t-shaped working model; coach engineers to be t-shaped, versatile, and take responsibility outside their core disciplines;
line management (1:1 meetings, personal development & training plan, career path, probation reviews, and performance reviews);
coach teams in applying scrum and devops;
be responsible for continuous improvement of the teams;
lead initiatives for implementing efficient development and delivery processes;
drive a learning-based culture with an ability to set and gain agreement for realistic and stretching objectives for the team.
technical environment:
microservices architecture system
programming - java, javascript, mv* patterns, nodejs, reactjs (including redux), c#, net framework 4.7, etc. asp.net, mvc
devops – jenkins, artifactory, sonarqube, github, cloudformation
cloud: multi-cloud, aws (lambda, postgres, s3, api gateway, cli, sns/sqs), azure

YeuCau:
have degree in computer science or related fields;
2+ years experience in java;
strong foundation & engineering skills. experienced in building high-performing systems;
good knowledge of data structures, system design and algorithms;
experienced working with cloud services such as gcp, aws, azure is a plus;
experience with web servers, caching solution such as redis;
be familiar with rdbms such as mysql/postgresql or nosql databases such as cassandra, mongodb is a plus.

MoTa:
#momo is the market leader in mobile payments in vietnam. we strive to make all transactions fast, easy and joyful. on a daily basis, we serve millions of transactions for a growing customer base of over 30 million people. momo’s service is especially helpful in rural areas where banking services are less prevalent.if you are looking for a place to grow your career and impact millions of people, momo might be just the right place for you.
developing and enhance large scale systems using java technologies: ai/gamification and promotion/ota/finance service — help momo scale business and services. working with the cloud computing tech stack.
driving technical collaborations with tech, business, product teams
designing the architecture for our new products and services;
delivering at all phases of the software lifecycle;
researching and developing new technologies, focus on mobile;
providing technical guidance and coaching to junior members
for domain ai, develop systems, services that serve machine learning models.

